cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper is about learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm, which involves optimization and modeling, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are covered by cs.CL and cs.CV. Finally, the paper uses large datasets and experiments, which are related to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS a possible sub-category.
